[thinking] I'm wondering if a proxy mock maker can use @InjectMocks with a concrete final class. It doesn't seem to mock a concrete class; rather, @InjectMocks creates an instance of it directly via MemberAccessor. That's usually okay, but the service has a private constructor, which may need instrumentation to access. Perhaps the metadata for the constructor is missing, causing a failure, or maybe tests aren't even running due to external configurations not capturing new class interfaces. This is all quite complex!
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Examining active class coverage**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm trying to figure out how to cover the active class. It seems that this needs to happen during the agent JVM run, but the coverage isn’t effective after it's been turned native. I’m wondering if setting the system property `org.mockito.internal.noUnsafeInjection` would help. I think it might be worth searching through upstream tests for `InstrumentationMemberAccessor` to see if there are any clues or solutions there. This is definitely quite the puzzle!
[thinking] 
